Reasoning: The paper deals with graph invariants and their values for digraphs and their symmetric versions. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The study of graph transformations to remove certain configurations also suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of conjectures and partial results indicates a focus on numerical analysis (cs.NA) and the study of extremal graphs suggests a connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
